      "message": "Patch Set 2: Code-Review+1\n\n> 802 is a failure due to non patched kernel being used.\n > I suggest at this point to use EXCEPT=\"802\". sanity 802\n > test still is expecting a dev_rdonly patched kernel even\n > though we have moved to dm-flakey.\n\nJames, could you please elaborate on this?  The \"-o rdonly_dev\"\nmount option has nothing to do with dev_rdonly or dm-flakey,\nbut rather is related to mounting a snapshot read-only.  In any\ncase, all of that is on the server, and the Ubuntu kernel is only\non the client, so it shouldn't affect the test at all.",
